 ZywOo | 

 pranavlko

                        
You can google buccholz score, but in this tournament's context, buccholz score of a team is calculated by adding the raw scores of all the teams that team has played against. ( Raw score of a team is number of wins minus number of losses. 1-3 team's raw score is -2 )
For example, nip have played Endpoint, BNE, CPH, Sinners. These 4 teams have win loss records as follows 1-3 , 2-2 , 3-0 , 2-2. So their raw scores are -2, 0, +3, 0. 
Nip's CURRENT buccholz score is then, (-2) + (0) + (+3) + (0) = +1. 
In any 16 team swiss stage, 3 teams end up 3-1. It was decided for EU RMR B that out of the 3 teams with 3-1 score, the team with least buccholz score after the swiss stage has completed will go straight to the challenger stage and the other 2 will play each other for a spot in the legends stage.
